</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="52C4F457EADF0F45FE6FC5AE7B4C2B46" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DEA1BC589FD5A3221398E9C04D6C5A86" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2CF7AF2F945121AE23D7420DB89BC7B" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Body piceous with green brassy reflections. Elytral surface with isodiametric mesh pattern, striae complete, punctures absent, 3 setiferous punctures on interval 3. Abdominal sternum VII with 4+4 setiferous punctures.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E65B6C89B3873D8B11FB8B2BBC3D803A" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" type="habitus">
<paragraph id="CDB7311C2A846D88A25F2726C950DB95" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Habitus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2F26146FA488F0DAF0146C7943AC0E1" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">
dorsal aspect, as in 
<figureCitation id="12C528313B4CB77B1E5B18A2F30E2ABD" captionStart="Figures 51–52" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 51 - 52. 51 Semiardistomis cyaneolimbatus (Chevrolat) 52 Semiardistomis pallipes (Dejean). Dorsal aspect. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/19673" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F63EA53EC670B6309C19FEED8FF83A5F" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" type="measurements and variation">
<paragraph id="C4DFA76CAAF2FE50C7FCD642C7AFBA11" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Measurements and variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1779CBD046E29C21D2A793478D7552F2" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">
Variation of measurements (mm) and ratios for 
<taxonomicName id="18436D83F79B76B036155014C1562694" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Semiardistomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipes">
<emphasis id="B82D279B40C93A8ED9DF1E687D8FEA15" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Semiardistomis pallipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n=12) are: HL = 0,44-0,54-0,66; PL 0,86-1,01-1,20; PW 0,92-1,10-1,34; EL 2,30-2,74-3,24; EW 1,48-1,72-2,00; SBL 3,70-4,30-5,10; PW/EW 0,64; PW/PL 1,09; PL/EL 0,37; EW/EL 0,63. More western specimens have complete elytral striae, whereas in those from the Amazon Basin the striae are shorter (
<figureCitation id="A8CAED91DC1EE074934C130FEA401740" captionStart="Figure 58" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 58. Distribution map, illustrations of exemplar left elytra, and variability of members of the labialis species-group in South America. Value inside symbol indicates portion of basal elytra in which striae are impressed, (C, complete impressed). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/19678" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F36E5A78D5F10B01FABFDE973874BEE" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" type="geographical distribution">
<paragraph id="E36D58417FDE2E5A524E279E2C477B9A" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Geographical distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E0F206366D901598CD2896DF6643FDDD" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">
(
<figureCitation id="B9233797CAD914E5A50C6EB167A9F36A" captionStart="Figure 58" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 58. Distribution map, illustrations of exemplar left elytra, and variability of members of the labialis species-group in South America. Value inside symbol indicates portion of basal elytra in which striae are impressed, (C, complete impressed). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/19678" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
)
<emphasis id="A0B9B6DC0322DD89EB23E6344878F691" bold="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">.</emphasis>
The range of this species extends in South America from northern Brazil and eastern Ecuador north to Colombia, and to Panama in Middle America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8702C0FE4DACD612AB6F2CDA166F9200" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="4181B43C81BD769CB4299762D49C893D" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">
<pageBreakToken id="5AE6F69C6F53B80D6202D54DAE00338F" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" start="start">Habitat</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3097E468E7F6E88D5DA879AF7CD5C758" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">
Label data indicate that specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="32C1F58651BAEFB1CB99FD27C593BE79" authorityName="Kult" authorityYear="1950" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Semiardistomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7E329642D15468EAAF1BD58B9A657915" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">Semiardistomis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pallipes were collected at margins of water bodies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
